DOCUMENT();

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGstandard.pl",
           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "MathObjects.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "parserNumberWithUnits.pl",
          # "parserFormulaWithUnits.pl",
          # "parserFormulaUpToConstant.pl",
	   "AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
	   "PGcourse.pl",
          );

TEXT(beginproblem());

Context("Numeric");

$a = random(1.25,3,.25);
$length = random(4,9,1);
$s = $a*$length;

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

What is the length of an arc cut off by an angle of $a radians on a
circle of radius $length inches?
$PAR
\{ ans_rule(18) \} (include units: \{ AnswerFormatHelp("units") \})
$BR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS( NumberWithUnits( $s, 'in' )->cmp() );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$PAR

The arc length, \( s \), corresponding to an angle of \( \theta \) radians in a circle of radius \( r \) is \( s = r \cdot \theta \).
$PAR
Thus our arc length is \( s = ( $length ) ( $a ) = $s \mbox{in} \)
$BR
END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


COMMENT('MathObject version');
ENDDOCUMENT();
